    "overview": "A polynomial is an algebraic expression where variables have non-negative integer powers. The degree is the highest power of the variable.",
    "keyPoints": [
      "Variables must have whole number exponents (0, 1, 2...).",
      "Degree = Highest power of the variable.",
      "Classification: Linear (deg 1), Quadratic (deg 2), Cubic (deg 3)."
    ],
    "detailedContent": "Polynomials are fundamental in algebra. For example, 2x^2 + 3x - 5 is a polynomial because the powers of x are 2 and 1 (whole numbers). However, 1/x or sqrt(x) are not polynomials because they involve negative or fractional powers. The degree of a polynomial determines its complexity and behavior."
